comments.body:
@dustymabe Right the UX sucks at the moment. However there is not much we can do at the moment. This error comes from CNI which executes iptables this fails. Our only possibility would be to string parse the error message in order to create a better one.
This might change with our new netavark network stack where we could create better errors, however we also use iptables commands there so I expect the same error. I think this is another reason why we should implement nftables support for netavark.

I think the needed modules are different when iptables-nft is used vs iptables-legacy. Loading modules by default on boot makes sense too me when other applications no longer load it for us. I am not sure if we need a systemd unit, adding the needed modules to `/etc/modules-load.d` should work too.

I just installed f36 and default is iptables-nft where it will work out of the box. It looks like the nf_tables module can be loaded by an unprivileged user so we do not have to add this explicitly.
@lucab @dustymabe Is there any reason why FCOS uses iptables-legacy in the first place?

Since old upgrades might still use iptables-legacy I will add the `ip_tables` and `ip6_tables` modules to the list but I am not sure if we want to keep this is the long run.
